post_text:
COVID-19 persists and continues to illuminate the structural challenges of our time. While we are saddened that the NorCal AIDS Cycle has been postponed until 2021, we recognize the difficulty and the full weight of that decision. While we won‚Äôt be coming together for this incredibly special event this year, there are still ways to support the ride and those in the Sacramento region who have been affected by HIV/AIDS. The best part? One of easiest is by doing what you are already doing anyway!

NCAC has setup an Amazon Smile account, which when you connect your Amazon account to it, will automatically donate .5% of your purchase to the NorCal Aids Cycle. More details in the post below.

Are you connected to Amazon Smile?
shared_text:
NorCal AIDS Cycle
June 22 at 8:49 PM ¬∑

You can now support the NorCal AIDS Cycle via Amazon Smile on the Amazon app! Here's how:

1. Open the app.
2. Go to Settings.
3. Tap 'AmazonSmile' and follow the instructions.
4. Choose ‚ÄòNorCal AIDS Challenge‚Äô as your charity.

Whenever you shop, Amazon will donate 0.5% of your purchase price the NorCal AIDS Cycle.

As of May 2020 you‚Äôve helped raise nearly $900 for NCAC through AmazonSmile!

One of the benefits of cycling, and why it‚Äôs so fun for kids in particular, is that you don‚Äôt need a lot of equipment to get started. Even a hand-me-down can do the trick. As we get more serious about cycling as a sport, gadgets and accessories make the experience more enjoyable, we want to stay on the bike longer, and goals can become realized.

What is the one thing you don‚Äôt want to ride without? That would make you turn around and head home to get?

In the wake (or the midst, depending where you are) of the COVID-19 shutdown, statistics are showing that cycling is making a comeback for casual riders interested in exercise, transportation, and socially-distanced group recreation.

A recent article from Cycling Weekly poses the question about diversity in cycling. We know there are barriers beyond just finances that keep people from owning a bike. Our friends at San Diego VeloYouth have been working for years on a program that helps make cycling more available to a wider audience, with a values-based program that serves at-risk kids by infusing goal-setting, cycling and daily achievement.

üîÜ How did you get interested in cycling?
üîÜ What can we do in the cycling community to make cycling more accessible, particularly for kids?

This past weekend Padres Pedal the Cause hosted a virtual cycling event to raise money to accelerate cancer research. The team over at Holland Cycles put their heads together and formed Team Bill Holland, in honor of Bill and his journey as he begins treatment for his recent diagnosis.
‚ú®

Not only did Team Bill Holland, (that‚Äôs you, that‚Äôs all of us!) raise $16,335 dollars for the #Do20Give20 campaign while getting out the door and riding, every single dollar we raised is being matched. That means every donation made by you or on your behalf will be doubled! Our grand total raised for the team was $32,670!
‚ú®

Our team of 120 registrants/donors was part of the 640 individuals who participated in the event this year. Collectively, we helped to raise over $118,000 through this campaign to fund collaborative research teams in San Diego and support the passion and commitment in creating A World Without Cancer!
‚ú®
Did you participate virtually with us on Saturday? Drop a photo in the comments from your ride!

post_text: It is with great regret that The Paso Robles Cycling Festival (a.k.a. The Great Western Bicycle Rally) scheduled for May 22 to 25, 2020 is cancelled. We will return next year with the date already set for May 28 to 31, 2021. With the federal mandate on public gathering in effect, we believe that the health and safety of all the volunteers and participants is critical. The terrible and dangerous situation with COVID-19 warrants this cancellation and rather than wait and see if the federal mandate for public gathering will lift by late May, we feel it is important to be proactive. Everyone who has registered for the 2020 event has received an email with more information about the cancellation and refund/rollover/transfer options. We will miss seeing our Festival cycling community in Paso this May, and we thank you for your understanding and for your support. Wishing you all the greatest health and safety. See you in Paso in 2021!
text: It is with great regret that The Paso Robles Cycling Festival (a.k.a. The Great Western Bicycle Rally) scheduled for May 22 to 25, 2020 is cancelled. We will return next year with the date already set for May 28 to 31, 2021. With the federal mandate on public gathering in effect, we believe that the health and safety of all the volunteers and participants is critical. The terrible and dangerous situation with COVID-19 warrants this cancellation and rather than wait and see if the federal mandate for public gathering will lift by late May, we feel it is important to be proactive. Everyone who has registered for the 2020 event has received an email with more information about the cancellation and refund/rollover/transfer options. We will miss seeing our Festival cycling community in Paso this May, and we thank you for your understanding and for your support. Wishing you all the greatest health and safety. See you in Paso in 2021!

This July we‚Äôll be joining Prouty Page for The Friends of Norris Cotton Cancer Center and their start/finish host King Arthur Flour for the 39th Annual The Prouty. The Silver State 508 has been dubbed ‚ÄúThe Toughest 48 Hours in Sport.‚Äù And for good reason. This journey through Nevada is not only challenging in mileage, but participants also endure hours of climbing, blazing desert sun and heat with no shade, night time temperatures that often drop below freezing and headwinds that build throughout the returning leg.

When you decide to register for this ride, you should be prepared both mentally and physically. So here is what we need to know in order for you to qualify:

üëâHave you entered (and completed) any events that lasted more than 24 hours? We would like to see proof that you can handle yourself on a bike for 30+ hours with little to no sleep.
üëâWill you be riding with a support crew?
üëâIf so, does your team have experience in ultra racing?
üëâIf not, we‚Äôll send you a required template to submit a race plan for approval for your self-supported ride.

Think you‚Äôre ready for the 508? Registration is open! Head to the link below for more details and to submit your application.

We hear all the time how cycling has changed people‚Äôs lives. We love your stories of getting on a bike after injury to help with recovery, signing up for a charity ride that builds community on and off the saddle, or a competitive race that instilled confidence and increased fitness to make you a happier and healthier member of your family and community, and even tales of touring the world on two wheels.

We‚Äôd love to hear what inspired you to get on a bike! Did you start riding as a kid and never stop? Or maybe you were nudged into the sport later in life. Let us know and tag your cycling buddies so we can hear their stories, too!

post_text:
Since its inception, the annual Padres Pedal the Cause has raised over $10 million dollars and every penny of each donation is used to fund collaborative research and clinical trials among San Diego‚Äôs top cancer research and treatment centers; including UC San Diego Moores Cancer Center, Sanford Burnham Prebys Medical Discovery Institute, Salk Institute, and San Diego Rady's Children‚Äôs Hospital.

People ride year after year because this cause is so near and dear to their heart. 1-in-3 of us will be diagnosed with cancer in our lifetime. In some way, this disease will touch all of our lives: every person, every family, every community.

Last year the event raised over $1.8 million dollars and we are honored to be part of this event again this year and can‚Äôt wait to see you on November 16th! Padres Pedal the Cause 2019

See some of the veteran teams that have been doing this ride for multiple years in the comments below!
Photo Credit: Padres Pedal the Cause

post_text:
A 620-mile ride down the California Coast would be hard enough without a squad of helpful support staff along the way. Did you know CCSD provides consulting services? We are partnering with the Challenged Athletes Foundation and bringing our A-Team to assist the over 100 cyclists, including 17 #CAFAthletes, who are starting this epic trip in just a few days. Some riders are joining us for the first time, others have been making this journey for years. We are packing up our SAG vans and the infamous lunch truck and can't wait to meet all of you in Palo Alto!

Need help planning your sports event? We'd love to help! Contact Rob at robert@ccsd.com for details.

#morethanaride #itsthejourney #mdc #caf #challengedathletesfoundation mailto:robert@ccsd.com

shared_text:
The Great Western Training Program
September 29, 2018 at 9:28 PM ¬∑

The Great Western Training Program (GWTP) 2018-2019

The Great Western Training Program has been going on for more than 30 years and it welcomes any rider in the San Diego cycling community or from above.

The program follows the same guideline that has been a tradition during all these years and any new participant will have the opportunity to chat with many of the experienced riders that have been participating in this program over the years.

We will also have the support of friends of the Great Western Training Program like Adam‚Äôs Avenue Bicycle store, Todd Boussom, SPOT and other volunteers that will help with neutral support during the ride to assist athletes mechanically to achieve their training goals.

The program promotes cooperation over competition, although we can be competitive with each other at times. Safety is the key word for the program and every rider will be participating at his own risk.

This year, the GWTP will have the support and presence of qualified and accomplished coaches at the start of every ride to describe the recommended workout for each Sunday.

post_text: Anyone who did St Paddy's Palomar Punishment this weekend. Photographs are up. Some great shots in there that really capture the Punishment and the fun. Mike charges a very reasonable $5 for each photograph. Click on the link below to view and purchase.
shared_text:
MIGHTYMIKEKURTZ.SMUGMUG.COM
Palomar Punishment 2017 - MightyMikeKurtz

Mike Kurtz shared a link to the event: St Paddy's Palomar Punishment.
March 13, 2017 at 12:08 PM ¬∑

The photos for Palomar Punishment 2017 are finally up (there was a ton of photos)
This year we (Claire and myself) shot more photos from more locations than ever !! It was a lot of work but I think the photos are fantastic. There are 9 galleries of photos to enjoy and purchase ($5 each !!!) Look through the photos , remember the fun and suffering you did. It was a huge accomplishment. Buy photos to share , post and brag about what you did !!
You can also look through previous years. I have been so lucky to have been doing the photos since 2013 for Josephine Allen and Robert Panzera. Any of the older photos are priced at $2.50. If you were a part of them or know anyone who was (tell them) , buy a photo on sale !!
Thank you to everyone !!!!

post_text: Thanks to everyone who showed up and rocked it at St Paddy's Palomar Punishment yesterday. What a fun day! My favorite comments from the finish "SPPP is like childbirth" and "OMG. How do you say Holy Cr@p in Irish". Thanks to Nature's Bakery and KIND Snacks for providing great nutritious food out there and WD-40 BIKE for the Pot o Gold loop prizes. Cyclists Massage for rescuing those tired bodies at the finish' San Diego VeloYouth for staffing the SAG on Palomar and Mavic and Bookabikemechanic.com for keeping you on the road (or helping you get off it!). Credit to Stone Brewing for allowing us to use Stone Farms. In case you didn't know Stone actually sold the farm the day before our event but still made sure that the event went ahead. That beer at the finish was so deserved and Highland Way were excellent as usual, providing finish line music. Finally thanks to our fantastic team of volunteers and staff. You made the event! Photographs from Mike Kurtz will be posted here this afternoon and available to purchase for just $5 each. KOM winners will also be posted later today.

post_text: If you are in #Sacramento area on January 31, check out this amazing gear swap and fundraising event for NorCal AIDS Cycle at The Coffee Garden at 2pm. It'll be fun, social, and a chance to meet up with folks riding for a great cause. If you have tubes, tires, seats, gear, gloves, clothing, speedometers, bike racks, locks, lights, clips, shoes, or any other cycling items you no longer use, then bring it to the swap. You can gift it to someone who CAN use it, and there's a good chance you'll find a treasure the YOU just must have! Refreshments and Raffle Prizes will also be available.
shared_text:

text:
If you are in #Sacramento area on January 31, check out this amazing gear swap and fundraising event for NorCal AIDS Cycle at The Coffee Garden at 2pm. It'll be fun, social, and a chance to meet up with folks riding for a great cause. If you have tubes, tires, seats, gear, gloves, clothing, speedometers, bike racks, locks, lights, clips, shoes, or any other cycling items you no longer use, then bring it to the swap. You can gift it to someone who CAN use it, and there's a good chance you'll find a treasure the YOU just must have! Refreshments and Raffle Prizes will also be available.

Reminder, please share:
Matt Hoffmann RAAM: The Movie
Sunday, October 25 The Ken Cinema at 12noon
4061 Adams Ave, San Diego, CA 92116

Come one and come all to see the excellent movie about Matthew Hoffmann RAAM. Behind the scenes footage, plus a Q&A with Matt himself and some of the actual kids in the SD VeloYouth program. 100% of donations go directly to San Diego VeloYouth. The movie and event are FREE. We have a suggested donation of $20 or more, if you feel inclined, that can be handed in via cash, check, or card on site.

Please spread the word and bring friends and family. The theater holds 192 people. Concession stands will be open.

Thank you so much for your support and interest. Matt would love to see you there!

Router Needed For Challenged Athletes Foundation New York City Charity Ride, Oct 2 to 4, 2015. This weekend! Paid at $150/day, plus all meals and lodging.

Router will drive course starting at 10am on Friday, Oct 2, putting up signs at turns and route arrows where needed for the event on Saturday.

On Saturday, Router will check signs from Friday, then route signs for Sunday.

On Sunday, Router will check signs from Saturday.
Ideally, this is a two person job: one driving and one putting up signs.

Contact Robert@ccsd.com or 917-543-2670.

post_text: So excited to be a part of this epic team challenge coming up in September. Lance Weir and David Lee with be the first hand cyclists to complete Silver State 508, a 508 mile race through Nevada with a 48 hour time limit. We'll be posting updates as we spend these final weeks prepping for what is sure to be a HUGE achievement by these guys. Also riding as part of the tandem team will be Rodney Boyd, Team Chase Boyd, Glen Plake and Zach Thorpe. Support crew includes Jared Wyllie, Matthew Hoffmann, Bill Walton, Caroline Pleitez Boyd along with some excellent physicians and PTs to keep these guys moving along.
